# Cursor Config Surface

- Keep rules concise and scoped by directory or file pattern when possible.
- Prefer nested rules for app-specific guidance instead of putting everything in root rules.
- Skills should be workflow-oriented, not copies of the same always-on rules.
- Subagents should have clear specialization and avoid overlapping ownership.
- Hooks should be safe to run often and must not rewrite user code without clear intent.
- MCP config should stay valid JSON and use project-relative paths when local servers are added.
